[h1]CSS3 Animations[/h1]

An animation lets an element gradually change from one style to another.
You can change as many CSS properties as you want to, as many times you want to.
[b]Keyframes [/b]hold the styles the element will have at certain times

[h2]The @keyframes Rule[/h2]

When you specify CSS styles inside the @keyframes rule, the animation will gradually change from the current style to the new style at certain times.
To get an animation to work, you must bind the animation to an element.

The following example will change the background color of an element three times: when the animation is 50% complete, 70% complete, and when the animation is 100% complete.

[b]The CSS:[/b][code format="css"]@keyframes example {
   [b]0%[/b]  {background-color: red;}
   [b]50%[/b]  {background-color: yellow;}
   [b]70%[/b]  {background-color: blue;}
   [b]100%[/b] {background-color: green;}
}[/code]
[note][b]example [/b]is the name of the animation. You can choose any name for your animation.[/note]

[h1]The @keyframes Rule[/h1]

As an alternative to using percentages, you can use [b]from [/b]and [b]to [/b]keywords, where:
[b]from[/b] is a starting offset of [b]0%[/b]
[b]to [/b]is an ending offset of [b]100%[/b].

The two examples below are equivalent, and produce the same result: [code format="css"]@keyframes colorchange {
   [b]0%[/b] {background-color: red;}
   [b]100%[/b] {background-color: green;}
}[/code]
[code format="css"]@keyframes colorchange {
   [b]from[/b] {background-color: red;}
   [b]to[/b] {background-color: green;}
}[/code]

[h1]The @keyframes Rule[/h1]

To get an animation to work, you must bind the animation to an element.
In the example below, the animation lasts one second, and changes the background color of the red div to green and blue.[code format="css" codeId="630"]div {
   width: 100px;
   height: 100px;
   background-color: [b]red[/b];
   [b]animation-name:[/b] colorchange;
   [b]animation-duration:[/b] 1s;
}
@keyframes colorchange {
   [b]0%[/b] {background-color: [b]red[/b];}
   [b]50%[/b] {background-color: [b]green[/b];}
   [b]100%[/b] {background-color: [b]blue[/b];}
} 
[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2715" width="100%"]
The [b]animation-name[/b] property specifies the animation to be used for the element.
The [b]animation-duration[/b] property specifies the duration of the selected animation. 
[note] If the animation-duration property is not specified, the animation will have no effect, because the default value is 0.[/note]
